      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OHOPE WINS (1) Group 1 New Zealand Oaks winner over 2400m at Ellerslie having her first start for the Waller stable. Five weeks between runs and kept up to the mark with a soft 1050m trial at Randwick. Big striding filly with a good turn of foot. BELLE CHEVAL (2) comes across from New Zealand fourth-up and yet to be tested past 1600m. Launched from near last on the turn with a desperately unlucky second in the LR The Kiwi over 1500m at Ellerslie. Can race closer to the speed from the better gate. Top-three prospect. SALTY PEARL (3) on target for this after she demolished inferior opposition with a slick win over 1600m in the Vobis Platinum Guineas at Caulfield two weeks ago. Group 2 winner in the Spring capable of testing the top two. PANOVA (4) warmed up late from back in the field with a tidy fifth over 1500m in the G2 Phar Lap Stakes second-up. Awkward map but not to be underestimated. LONG LEGS (6) both runs back have been satisfactory and stays in the mix with her on-pace style.",
